commit.message:
collection: col_allocate_item() make sure COL_TYPE_STRING can be
NULL terminated.

Resolves: https://github.com/SSSD/ding-libs/issues/20

Reviewed-by: Sumit Bose <sbose@redhat.com>

SPEC: specify ini_config dependencies versions

Reviewed-by: Iker Pedrosa <ipedrosa@redhat.com>
release.sh: adjust to new version naming scheme
Update version before 0.6.2 release

tests: fixed following compilation warnings:
```
path_utils/path_utils_ut.c:354:31: warning: ‘/foo/bar’ directive output may be truncated writing 8 bytes into a region of size between 1 and 4096 [-Wformat-truncation=]
  354 |     snprintf(p2, PATH_MAX, "%s/foo/bar", cwd);
      |                               ^~~~~~~~
...
path_utils/path_utils_ut.c:302:31: warning: ‘/foo’ directive output may be truncated writing 4 bytes into a region of size between 1 and 4096 [-Wformat-truncation=]
  302 |     snprintf(p2, PATH_MAX, "%s/foo", cwd);
      |                               ^~~~
```

Reviewed-by: Sumit Bose <sbose@redhat.com>

dhash: removed senseless check

Reviewed-by: Sumit Bose <sbose@redhat.com>

CONFIGURE: explicitly require GETTEXT version

This is required by `autopoint` executed by `autoreconf`

Resolves: https://github.com/SSSD/ding-libs/issues/8

Reviewed-by: Pawel Polawski <ppolawsk@redhat.com>
Reviewed-by: Sumit Bose <sbose@redhat.com>

CONFIGURE: fix AM_GNU_GETTEXT usage

Fixed following autoreconf issue:
```
ERROR: Use of AM_GNU_GETTEXT without [external] argument is no longer supported
```

Reviewed-by: Pawel Polawski <ppolawsk@redhat.com>
Reviewed-by: Sumit Bose <sbose@redhat.com>

*.pc.in: update URL

Resolves: https://github.com/SSSD/ding-libs/issues/9

Reviewed-by: Pawel Polawski <ppolawsk@redhat.com>

Add `test_rules.ini` (autogenerated by `make check`) to `.gitignore`

Reviewed-by: Pawel Polawski <ppolawsk@redhat.com>

INI: suppress false positive coverity warning

`get_str_cfg_array()` returns `char **array` that is composed of pointers
to slices of `copy` so `copy` can't be freed here.

Reviewed-by: Pawel Polawski <ppolawsk@redhat.com>

PATH_UTILS: suppress false positive warnings

Warnings are false positives: every such `strncpy` is followed
by an explicit check that result is NULL-terminated.

Reviewed-by: Pawel Polawski <ppolawsk@redhat.com>

INI: fix check for error code

In case of fail `asprintf()` returns -1, not 1.

Fixes following covscan issues:
```
Error: RESOURCE_LEAK (CWE-772): [#def1]
ding-libs-0.6.1/ini/ini_configmod.c:869: alloc_arg: "asprintf" allocates memory that is stored into "strval". [Note: The source code implementation of the function has been overridden by a builtin model.]
ding-libs-0.6.1/ini/ini_configmod.c:873: leaked_storage: Variable "strval" going out of scope leaks the storage it points to.
 #  871|           TRACE_ERROR_NUMBER("Asprintf failed.", ret);
 #  872|           /* The main reason is propbaly memory allocation */
 #  873|->         return ENOMEM;
 #  874|       }
 #  875|
```

Reviewed-by: Pawel Polawski <ppolawsk@redhat.com>

validators_ut_check: Fix fail with new glibc

Error message was slightly change from previous version
of glibc which caused fails in validators unit tests.

Reviewed-by: Jakub Hrozek <jhrozek@redhat.com>

path_utils_ut: allow single / as well

From http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/009695399/basedefs/xbd_chap03.html#tag_03_266
  Multiple successive slashes are considered to be the same as one slash.

When running the tests on a musl libc system
 get_dirname(p, PATH_MAX, "//foo//")
actually results in a / and not //

Reviewed-by: Michal Židek <mzidek@redhat.com>

Add note about AM_GNU_GETTEXT_VERSION

Reviewed-by: Michal Židek <mzidek@redhat.com>

Move LIBICONV/INTL additions to _LIBADD not _LDFLAGS

Reviewed-by: Michal Židek <mzidek@redhat.com>

Add iconv/lintl to libpath_utils

Reviewed-by: Michal Židek <mzidek@redhat.com>

Use autoconf to check for the need for libintl/libiconv

Reviewed-by: Michal Židek <mzidek@redhat.com>

Non-GNU ld doesn't have --version-script support

Reviewed-by: Michal Židek <mzidek@redhat.com>

BUILD: BuildRequire gettext-devel

This is needed to build RPM after the patches from
https://github.com/SSSD/ding-libs/pull/4/ are applied.

Reviewed-by: Michal Židek <mzidek@redhat.com>
Merges: https://pagure.io/SSSD/ding-libs/pull-request/3188

INI: add doxygen refs to flags of some functions

Signed-off-by: Ivan Wagner <wagner17@mandalore.com>
Reviewed-by: Michal Židek <mzidek@redhat.com>
Merges: https://pagure.io/SSSD/ding-libs/pull-request/3187

CONFIGURE: Get rid of bashism

Reviewed-by: Michal Židek <mzidek@redhat.com>

INI: Fix detection of error messages

libc on BSD returns different error messages.

Reviewed-by: Michal Židek <mzidek@redhat.com>

INI: Fix compilation of unit tests

man 3 wait says that the header file "sys/wait.h" needs to be included
for the macro WEXITSTATUS

Reviewed-by: Michal Židek <mzidek@redhat.com>

Ignore all the extra built files

Reviewed-by: Lukas Slebodnik <lslebodn@redhat.com>

Remove references to malloc.h which isn't used; but use stdlib.h instead

Reviewed-by: Lukas Slebodnik <lslebodn@redhat.com>

INI: Remove definiton of TRACE_LEVEL

Macros TRACE_LEVEL 7 and TRACE_HOME should only be defined
in testing builds where we want debug messages to be generated.

The macros are leftovers from the previous patch where they
were improperly added for debug purposes.

Resolves:
https://pagure.io/SSSD/ding-libs/issue/3182

Reviewed-by: Robbie Harwood <rharwood@redhat.com>
